commit.message:
Write gzipped data as binary

Be careful when writing binary data on Windows.

```
$ ruby -e 's = Gem::Util.gzip("\x04\x08[\x05".b); p s.index("\n"); puts IO::Buffer.for(s).hexdump'
6
0x00000000  1f 8b 08 00 6c 3d 0a 66 00 03 63 e1 88 66 05 00 ....l=.f..c..f..
0x00000010  e3 69 10 89 04 00 00 00                         .i......
```

commit.message: [gemspec_helpers] Fix Rubocop warning.
[build, rebuild] Split common find_gemspec() out to GemspecHelpers.
Improve formatting of "gem rebuild --help" output.
[rebuild] If --diff is not passed and a rebuild fails, suggest passing --diff.
[rebuild_command] Bail early if the RubyGems version doesn't match.
[rebuild_command] Use Gem.* helpers.
[rebuild_command] Clean up help text.
[rebuild_command] Use temporary directory instead of the working directory.
[rebuild_command] Add --diff flag to try using diffoscope.
[rebuild_command] Avoid leaking files.
Add "gem rebuild" command.
